\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When I married we lived in a - er - oh wait a minute - we didn't live in Highgate straight away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh well - all the brothers died. We had - I had - er - Pansy, Noele and Daisy - there were four girls lived and three brothers died.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Can you remember what the order of their births were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - that was a very beautiful boy at first, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Sidney
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and he died at seven years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was he much older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He was the first child - yes, you see, then - um - oh dear I don't remember the others. 
The others died as babies though, but - er - now my teacher sister was the eldest and she was eighteen months older than me and then the other two there was eighteen months between both of us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh goodness no. He was quite young. I can't remember exactly, no. Mother was very young - she was only twenty and father was a few years older - but I can't quite remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Your mother was twenty when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - I was not the first one born, you see, she was twenty when she married. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you know where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 My father was partly Irish - but they came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} I couldn't say when. He was half Irish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He came from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well
 he was in - oh yes, he'd been in London quite a long time - he was born in Ireland and was I think educated there then came to London, but I couldn't say when.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what did he do - what was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well he was a designer of men's clothes actually and he was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Bond Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and in those days they didn't - er - these very high class little places didn't advertise - they worked for the aristocracy, you see, and he was a designer of men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 s clothes, which he very much enjoyed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 That would have demanded an awful lot I think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I think he would have preferred to have done women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 s clothes but it was easier for him to get into - er - in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Is that the job he had all the time that he was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. 'Til he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He didn't do any other jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. No. No. He was very musical - he used to sing in the choir at All Saints church and he played the clarinet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Twenty when she married and
 I think it was about a year - a year afterwards when she had the first child - now there was the first child - boy - Sidney - he died - then she had two twins - she had twins - now - one lived and one died. She had them about, you know, sort of space of 
two years between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you came after \'85.. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I was - there was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Sidney{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and there was - yes there was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Sidney{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - there was Daisy - I was the third child. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So she'd be about twenty-four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Two years between would she be that - something like that. Why are these details so important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember where your mother came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. I know that they lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} but I think she originally came from the country. Yes. Her - her father was a journalist.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
No - she didn't you see, she married very young and - er - again she was a very good cook and domestic and she was the one who was kept at home. It was quite a common thing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how many rooms there were in the house where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 The house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Enfield{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - yes there were quite a lot - about - about - say nine or ten rooms, yes, you know it was quite a big house. With the attics. The rooms weren't as large as these but it was a - Cromwell house or a Victorian house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no. We had a grandfather with us for the last few y
ears - yes - my mother's father. He did live with us until he died, yes, after his own wife died, you see, we just had him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your mother have any help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, she used to have a woman in, you know, about once or twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what sort of things she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Mother - she was very good at cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - the lady who came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh she did the actual - actual - er - cleaning, you know, the cleaning of floors and - and sweeping - er - carpet sweeper and we
 didn't have hoovers I don't think then - er - just ordinary cleaning, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she help with the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, mother didn't want people to help with the children, she didn't like interference in that way, no. She did nothing for th
e children at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how you got on with her - do you remember the lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes - I think I always got on with people - she always used to call me dearie - um - I've always liked people - and she was a kindly sort of woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what did she call you and your brothers and sisters - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - she used to call me dearie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - Madam. Yes. Oh yes, Madam, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember whether washing was done at home in your house or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well, a certain amount was done at home - yes - and this woman used to do it - there was wash day you see, and there was an old copper and the things were boiled in the copper - there was in this house an old copper when we came there - I had -
 I got rid of it, yes, where things were boiled and so on. Yes there was a regular wash day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your mother or father mend or make any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, mother was very good with her needle indeed - she simply loved doing things. Er - she made quite a lot of our clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And your father designed clothes do did he ever give a hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, well he designed clothes for men, you see, but he didn't do anything for us because we were girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about shoes - did anybody make shoes in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - we had - er - um - bought shoes and we - er - had them mended, you know, at the cobblers, and so on yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. Not at all. Er - he - he wasn't expected to you see, no. No. Not anything at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He never bathed you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh never did anything like that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - yes - he used to read to us sometimes - especially 
to me because I was a very bad sleeper and had terrible hysterics and dreams and he used to come out at night and pat my hand - mother was very impatient about it all, you see. But I was a mischevious child and I was terribly afraid of going to hell, you 
s
ee, and I was afraid of going to sleep in case I burnt up. I suppose, you know, I brought up in the old way of the hell-fire and all that and being a very imaginative child I was terrified of going to sleep. I tried not to go to sleep and used to get hyst
erical and father used to come and sit and - and read to me a little and pat my had and he was very tired - I always remember that very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He sounds a nice person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh he was - my sisters were all much sturdier than I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did the older children help the younger children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes - a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have any tasks that you had to carry out regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Because I was so good at needlework that I was soon doing all the mending and very soon making things - I 
started making things very young. Well I was very good at dressing my dolls you see and mother notice that and got me on to other jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You sewed all by hand did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. We had a hand machine later on in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you go on helping out with those things until you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes, yes. Helped run the home and cook and all that. In fact I was very sorry I wasn't trained to go out and do something as I found it so dreary. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You said the older children helped the younger chi
ldren with things they found difficult. Do you remember for instance if they helped them to dress. Oh yes, yes. The elder ones helped the younger ones yes, yes. That was - that was quite common.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did the little ones help the older ones in any way at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh they would be asked to bring things - fetch things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh certainly - oh absolutely - that was very rigid. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. Until we get - got old enough to undress and mother would supervise our baths, you see, until we were old enough to do ourselves.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember at what age you were when you put yourself to bed first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 That's rather difficult to remember - such a long time ago - I don't think I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not the bed but the bedroom. Um - two of us slept in the bedroom, you see, two in each bedroom. And there were single beds. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We had a bathroom - oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how often you did as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh we had a bath most evenings - I think my mother was most exceptionally clean. Lots of people did only have a sort of weekly bath in those days, you know - at least three times a week we had a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Your mother was very particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh she was extremely particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember when you had clean clothes put on? Was it a regular weekly ritual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, yes, every week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh we had a large pleasant kitchen, but on Sunday we had it in the dining room. Yes, yes. But in the winter we always had it in the kitchen in the - in the weekdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh in the kitchen. She had a kitchen and a scullery, you see
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she have a range or a stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh she had a big old fashioned range, yes, yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh we had breakfast quite early - about seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What members of the family were present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We used to have it all together. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what you had for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - we had very simple breakfasts. We - we had porridge which I hated - see they didn't make all these fla
key things like - and I loathed porridge but I had to eat it. Porridge and bread and butter and marmalade and - when we got older bacon and eggs things like that. I was very unhappy with nearly all the food. But the others weren't so \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I remember having to eat tripe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh wasn't it ghastly stuff. Oh yes we had to eat it - because of course they kn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 w so little then about things - they thought getting it down and it - and it - er - performed the miracle. I was sick nearly every day actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have anything different on certain days, like Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes - we always had a special joint on Sunday - we always had fish on Friday. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what about mid-day meals as a child - do you remember what sort of things you ate at mid-day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes - there was cold meat for Monday and there was mince on Tuesday and then probably Wednesday there was - er - chops or something like that. I suppose - quite a variety. And Friday always fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And in the evening - what did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well we had very light meals in the evening - you see, we had a tea meal and then - er - we'd perhaps have soup or milk or something like that later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, she did very often. Not always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And bottled fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And bottled fruit - oh yes. All those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Vegetables, pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, she didn't pickle no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about home made wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, we were very strong teetotallers because the - some of the fami
ly died of drink, you see. Her own mother died of drink and - er - they were very, very strong teetotaller - I mean I never touched anything alcoholic and used to say I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 
never will and so on until I mar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 ried really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your mother make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes, she used to do a few things - a cough mixture I remember - we had coughs a lot in the winter. Er - I think there was aniseed and lemon and honey and things like that - old fashioned remedies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did your father or mother grow their own vegetables? And fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. No, they never grew any of that. They weren't interested in growing things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did they buy them or did they have tinned or dried fruit and vegetables.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh they didn't have many tinned things - they were mostly fresh th
ings bought - see there wasn't nearly as much tinning then as there is now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how many times a week you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh quite four or five times - yes. Yes. Mother didn't like - we
 did have a garden - big enough - but she didn't like having chickens and killing them and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I think father did have rather more - yes - he was quite a big man with big bones and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not much, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you had to eat what you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, had to be finished. We were tol
d of all the children who hadn't enough to eat and that sort of thing - and I said one day well couldn't we give it to the children who haven't enough to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did they say to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 They told me quiet and get on with my food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What would happen if you did leave something uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well, I had to eat it at tea. Oh yes. I was nearly always - I was - I was terribly delicate - I was sick nearly every day. But the others weren't - they were much stronger. And then I learnt to
 sort of eat it very quickly and then used to suffer with dreadful indigestion, but that was just me individually, you see. And I used to think when I grow up I won't eat this and that and I became an absolute food reformer when I grew up and studied diet
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
What happened if you wanted something at the table - like the salt - could you ask someone to pass it or did you have to wait until it was offered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You didn't reach across - you asked someone 'may I have the salt please'. Yes you had table \'85..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Could you ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - yes, you could - yes. In fact mother rather liked it because she was a good cook and it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Good if you asked for more - flattering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So you said they were very particular about table manners - you were made to hold your knives and forks and sit properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, yes. And not talk with your mouth full or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And when could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When the meal was - when everybody had finished. Oh yes. Then you'd say 'may I get up'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did all the family sit at the table in the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, we each had our own place, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how the meal was served - how it was served out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well the joint was put on the table and the vegetables in covered dishes and so on, you see, father always - er - cut - well I would say 
\'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He did the carving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. And mother serve out the vegetables. We didn't do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember where the younger brothers and sisters would sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, of course, when they were very young there was the high chair, I know the youngest one always had the meal in the high chair.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Would your mother feed them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes. Next to mother - yes. I suppose those high chairs have gone out. I don't know. They still have them - yes? Yes. Its a good idea - I think it makes the child freer you see, if they spill anything and \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
No. Er - mother was - er - very temperamental and very frustrated - she would have made a marvellous actress, you see, but she just married and had a domestic life and - but she used to be very g
ay very often and sing, we used to say sing operatics and she'd sing be gay. But she was very frustrated and sometimes very bitter because of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. She found it very difficult to show affection. Er - father was better
. When I terribly needed affection father would kiss me and tell me to try and be a good girl and all that but mother couldn't somehow - she couldn't show her affection - and I'm sure she was very fond of us in her way but she just couldn't show it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If you had any worries could you share them with her or would it be with \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But you would with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, I - I never told her any of my worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 With your father - would you have told him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well - I would if he'd as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 ked, you see. A little more sym}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 pathetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Um - well I think we were taught to be fair to each other - you know, not to grab too much of the - the s
hare and so on - and share our toys and \'85\'85..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Say another child hit you would you be told that you should hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I must try and remember that. I don't think we ever hit in front of mother because we were afraid of being pun - punished 
- we did that more when we were on our own. I think we kept that from mother really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, I really think they wanted us to be very good straight honourable people, and - e
r - very dependable all the real plain virtues, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did they bring you up to consider certain things as ver}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956  important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, it was important to be honest and to - er - work well and hard - er - of course I had a very difficult time
 because I was a very friendly child and if someone spoke to me and took my hand I'd walk off with them, you know, and somehow I always attracted men, right from a ch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 
ild, but I was a little undersiz}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 ed but lively child, with very long hair right down here -
 very dark - I wasn't considered beautiful but my - er - but painters and people always - admired me. I had a very beautiful sister - conventionally beautiful - she'd got auburn curly hair like mother - she became a teacher - she never married unfortunate
l
y and she lost all her beauty because she ever ate and neglected herself - she was a teacher and - er - but I was much more unconventional looking, you see, in fact - er - some Countess wanted to adopt me but my mother wouldn't allow it - er - she though 
it would be very unfair, you see, because I would be taken away and have a very rich life and it wasn't fair to the others. I respected her for that when I grew older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what your parents thought of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well father used to say
 damn when he was very - er - very angry - that was all - and then mother used to say 'shouldn't say that in front of the children' - so we didn't hear that language at all really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. Oh no. Not speak until we were spoken to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Be punished. Oh sometimes have a good hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And who would give it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh my father - yes. It was terrible - and I was usu
ally the one because I was much more adventurous that the others you see. I was sent for an errand I'd wander into another street perhaps and then of course that was found out - that I'd been too long and - sometimes I didn't always know the right change 
and - I had a lot of hidings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was it always your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes. It was awful - and I don't think he really liked doing it - I always had that feeling - but I just had my bottom smacked. In fact my sisters - the one sister who's alive - lives in 
Dorset now, see sometimes - you know when I come to think about it you did have a lot of hidings didn't you. I say I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your mother ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 She punished me by making me go without something I liked very much, you know, a jelly or 
something like that. She didn't hit us. Always left that to father
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, we always had - er - when we had a birthday it was very nice. All - everybody - all the other sisters in
 the house gave us something and we had a birthday cake. Oh yes, birthdays were always - er - nice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have parties with people from outside the family or was it just the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, it was generally a family - we weren't encouraged to h
ave friends very much, you know, father was very critical of other people and we - and I suppose being a fair size family - I made friends easily but - I wasn't encouraged to bring them home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about Christmas Days. Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes, we used to get - er - up little plays, you see, I was very keen on - er getting up plays, and - er - yes, I organized it - made the frocks and everything, sometimes wrote the little plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What the whole lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes. I often did the whole lot. Or we - of course there were a lot of plays we got and another thing we were very fond of doing - nigger minstrels and we used to black ourselves with soot. And - er - I used to make up all
 sorts of funny things. And mother let us do all that and enjoyed it very much - although it made a terrible - terrible mess. Well mother was very interested in dramatics really, as I say, she would have been a very good actress. Yes. So we always did tho
se sort of things together. Yes, we made nearly all our own enjoyments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. Father played - we had the piano and we all had piano lessons and father played the clarinet - I played the mandolin - 
er - we all played something - another sister played the piano and one played the banjo and we used to have our own music every Sunday. We - we had - we made our own music, you see, another one sang - um - we all did something - the whole family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Who was the one who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - er - the one who died - the teacher - she sang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you made a lot of music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Every Sunday we used to have music. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, they ne
ver played games with us, no. Oh, we used to play cribbage, of course. That's quite an old fashioned game - um - my father played chess, he was very fond of chess - I wasn't very fond of cribbage or chess, - er - but two of my sisters were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were there books in the house, lots of books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
We had a good many books, yes. Um - Dickens and Thackaray and all the old classics you know and Scott and all those. Yes we had all those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about newspapers, do you remember what newspapers they took?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes - um - conventional newspapers. Not Reynolds - that was too Labour - um - I forget what they were, but the ordinary conservative papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, we didn't have magazines very much. I think there were one or two - I
 can't remember what they were. I think mother had the Home Journal - is there something called the Home Journal - a woman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 s magazine you know - about making clothes and recipes and things like that. I forget what it was called. A weekly thing. Um - I don'
t think it was called. A weekly thing. Um - I don't think it was called Woman's Magazine then - I think that's a later thing - it was some kind of home journal. Yes - I can't remember what it was now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember your mother or father reading much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well mother used to read novels - father used to read books about travel - travelling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, they didn't - no. But, as I say, we had all the classics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do your remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
A funeral? Er - yes - er my mother's father lived with us for some years - the journalist one and - er - there was a funeral for him when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did the whole family go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We weren't allowed to go - no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what the mourning clothes were like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh - all - all black - yes. And I think we had white - white blouses and black. Everyone went into mourning, you know, for so long three-eighth I forget how long it was. It all depended on the relative - it was quite a time
 - yes it was. I used to like funerals - I liked the black horses, those beautiful black horses. Oh they were so lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When you were a child were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, not very much - we were - er - not - sort of a closed in family rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes. We were taken shopping sometimes, yes. And we were taught to go and do shopping - I had to do most of that 'cos I was quite good at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes, father used to take us cycling a lot - he taught us to cycle - we all had bicycles - we cycled all over the place - we loved that. Father was very patient teaching us to and we just loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember any other outings with your parents? Bank holidays - things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, not very much because they said the traffic was so bad, you see, we used to get up these plays and do things at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So you made your own amusements inside the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. All the time. But we did - on Sunday mornings when mother cooked - father used to take us out cycling - it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, we used to go to the sea-side every year - somewhere or other. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And the whole family went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what you did at the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh we mostly - we learnt to swim and play with the buckets and sand and all that sort of thing - just the usual things children do, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Can you tell me how you spent Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well Saturdays - Saturdays - well - there was the shopping and father used to take us out cycling Saturday afternoon - Sunday we had to go to church, of course, and Sunday school we had to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents go to church themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well, mother didn't always go - father used to take us - 'cos mother did the cooking on a Sunday - but she used to go sometimes. In the summer we'd sometimes have a cold - cold meal and she'd go, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What denomination were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh high church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. I didn't like it. It was so dull - didn't like it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was that in the morning or the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, there were some occasionally, we very rarely went though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What other sort of social activities organized by the church did you take part in - were there any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, not very much, I don't think there were so many things in those days. They didn't g
o in for dramatics and things - specially the high churches - er - very much in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did the church run a temperance club do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think some churches did - but we were very high church it the lower you know, what do they call i
t, the low church - did a - they did a lot more social work in that way - high church didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And who would say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And - er - oh father. Rather quickly on Sundays, you see, just to get 
on with the carving. And of course the nuns used to come and see us from the hi - from the church, you see, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - we didn't have family p
rayers but we always had to kneel beside our bed and ask God to forgive us for all our sins and all that sort of thing at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not very much, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You don't know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. I - he didn't talk about - I don't think he was politically minded really at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Neither was she, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember your mother or father voting in a General election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well they were Liberal - yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 In some places at that time men are supposed to have felt they risked losing their jobs if they voted differently from their employers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. That - er - that - er - was quite true - yes - there was a lot of fear and a lot of
 people didn't vote at all because of that. That kind of pressure was all right with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was he actually a member of the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, he didn't join it. No. Well he didn't want to give the time, you see, he was very fond of playing his c
larinet and so on. He loved music and singing - he wasn't very interested in politics really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
So when your parents weren't working - when your father wasn't working he would play his clarinet and he would take you out - did he have any other interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, yes, yes. No, I don't think he did much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what about your mother when she wasn't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh she was very busy, yes. Oh she used to sing and dance and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she have any interests actually outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she ever go out by herself to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 It didn't seem to be the thing in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, you always either went with your husband or you took the children - used to be taken to the pantomime or something lik
e that or mother and father would go to a theatre and so on but they didn't do any social work or anything outside the home really at all. There'd be a church bazaar - one would go to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember when your father got home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh the days were long - yes. Er - very long - I think he didn't - very often didn't get home 'til seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Would he spend every evening a week at home? Or would he go out sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - well - no - he used to take us out, you see, cycling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He didn't go to clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
No, he didn't belong to - he never felt he had the time, you see, well father really liked wine very much, but of course mother wouldn't allow it in the house, because - and she was afraid that if father too
k to it, you see, he would drink too much, because her parents you see died of drink.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did he take part in any sort of sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He was a volunteer for quite a long time, you know, yes, he used to love that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did that entail?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well, I don't quite know what - what volunteers did - they - they learnt to shoot and - er - mostly I suppose shooting, and they wore red coats and he was very fond of his red coat - yes I remember he was a - was a volunteer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did he ever go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, they didn't believe in races.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you know if your father or mother belonged to any savings clubs? Against sickness or funerals or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I believe they did - it was - the Prudential, I think. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well I was the odd one you see - I didn't quarrel with them - we didn't quarrel it - I was just so different, you see, but - um - I think we got on very well - you see, I used to get up these little plays 
which they loved and did the clothes and that sort of thing - we got on quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was there anyone you were particularly close to - any one of your brothers or sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I think the brother who died - I was very fond of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Sidney{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Mm. He was a lovely boy - he was very beautiful to look at too. Yes, I was very fond of him but you see I - I got a bad name very quickly and I was looked at rather askance because they was quite sure I was going the wrong - you know, on the wrong road.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You were rebellious were you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
I was rather rebellious, yes. Well, you see, it was awful feeling that you was destined somehow to be wicked and - er - I couldn't see how it was that I was so wicked because I was more adventurous and
 I used to pray to God to make me good like the others and of course - er - that was difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
You said earlier you didn't play much with other children because your mother was rather disapproving - you didn't play with neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, no. Mother was very keen on keeping ourselves to ourselves sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Where did you play in that case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh in the garden - the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what games you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We used to play ball and - er - ping-pong we used to pla
y that - we loved ping-pong - that was a game in the house though, of course, we loved ping-pong. We played ball mostly and we had a swing, you know, was very simple things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, not too dirty. We did have overalls to put on - that - I remember now we had overalls - when we went and played.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So generally your mother would discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 It was really in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, very much in the family - especially as there were several of us, you see. She was always afraid of bad influence or something.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were there any sort of youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, no. There may have been, I don't know, but we didn't belong to anythin
g. I think families were very self contained actually in those days - many of them were, because we seemed to follow a common pattern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about when you were at school - what about your free time then? Did you have any hobbies, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, I loved drawing and needlework, painting, reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh we - we always had a cat and we had a dog sometimes too. Father was very fond of dogs but mother didn't care for them. We always had a cat though. I adored anim
als of course - absolutely adored them. I remember the cat used to have cats meat on a skewer and it was put through the letterbox and the cat used to sit waiting for that for hours and it was in great pieces and he'd pull it off and eat it bit by bit and
 I used to feel sorry for it and think it ought to be cut up for him - and - mother was rather fierce with animals. But - er - I simply loved animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about collecting things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, I didn't collect very much, but one sister was very keen on collecting - um - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8980887\charrsid10370956 butterflies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
 and - um - what are these little creatures who - er - change into something - caterpillars - she was the one who became a teacher - she used to have a lot of caterpillars and one sister collected marbles - no I don't think I did collect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You were more active?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes. I collected poems. Oh yes, and used to write out poems several books of poems I had - I used to make up nursery rhymes - I've still got some nursery rhymes - quite a book of nursery rhymes - ones I wrote. 
No, I was always writing something - either little poems or nursery rhymes or little stories - sometimes with very sad endings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about things like gardening? Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - I didn't do any gardening - I just picked flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Or fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. No. No, I would have hated to catch anything alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You said that you went bicycling with your father a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you go walking with him as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, yes, we did too. Used to take us round a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you take part in any other sports?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I didn't but the others did. They played tennis all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When you were still a child did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not very much as a child - er - if there was a children's show we went - but the theatre was considered rather wicked and \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - well we did our own music mostly, you see, we did go to some concerts but er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you ever to to music-halls or \'85?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no. I longed to but\'85\'85\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And cinemas - were there cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh we did sometimes go to cinemas if they - if the programme was suitable, you see, if father went to see what they were like first of all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And then they'd let you go if it was all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, if it was suitable, yes, I remember enjoying that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We had very little, I forget what it was - something}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956  like two}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was that regular - every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes - then it went up to sixpence or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what you spent it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Sweets. Toffee apples - we had toffee apples - I don't know whether you ever see them now. They used to be quite nice. They lasted such a long time tool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You said that your mother had a home help but did she have anybody else to look after the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. No. She didn't believe in having other people anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well she was practically never ill - it's amazing - she did suffer wit
h rheumatism however - but mother was - oh she used to dance and do exercises and all that sort of thing. She was - er - she was very fit - healthy and fit - she never over ate - she lived to be ninety-three - I think she could - would have lived longer o
nly I think she was - er - you know, tired of life because she couldn't see very well then and - er - and then she got bed ridden but - er she danced a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 By herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. She used to make up dances and all that and - then she used to sing, as 
we called it, operatics and she was very lively. Was a rather passionate and difficult person though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about when your younger brothers and sisters were born how did she manage then, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well she was awfully domestic you know, I
 think she managed very well. Er - we had a regular routine you see and people worked very hard in those days - they really had a routine and kept to it got up early and - it's a question of whether you're well organized or not, isn't it, and she was.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have any relatives - did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We had very few relatives actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did any of them live near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. Unfortunately - except grandfather whom we disliked. Grandmother - mother's mother was
 a - a very delightful woman but she made the wrong marriage and so she got drink every day and she was so beautiful that the police used to take her - instead of taking her up - er - she'd got long dark ringlets - and she was so lovely they just used to 
carry her home instead of prosecuting her. But it was because she had such a dreadful husband, you see, grandfather would - never drank tea or coffee - he believed in water - Gods ale as he c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956 
alled it - he was a natural vege}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 tarian - he didn't believe in kill
ing anything and he was a journalist and he used to go off and leave grandmother you see, and mother grandmother took to drink because she was so lonely, I think. And he would just, you know, have sex with her and produce a child and so on and he had - he
 
was a very wicked man - he had a - er - a daughter who was a cripple and he had a child by his own daughter. It was dreadful - er - and this girl went on the streets because she said it was so dreadful - you she was so - and she was very plain - and fortu
n
ately - er - an uncle - er - who was terribly sorry for her - um - had a very nice Scotch friend - er - who - she solicited this Scotch friend - they were out together - and er - fortunately the Scotch friend fell in love with her and he married her. And 
redeemed her you see, our history's really rather dreadful. Well, there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
s quite a lot of things happen isn't there if you really know, yes, yes. And of course all that we daren't say anything about - you see I didn't even know about 'till long afterwards. No I think - those things happened but they were - not publicised.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So you didn't see much of your relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, very little. We didn't have very many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents have friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, not many, no. They had a few, but very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did they share the same friends? Or would they have different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - no - er - father had men friends and mother had women - women friends you see. But - er - was very \'85..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Where would your mother see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh well come to tea
 sometimes or she would - er - perhaps go to a jumble sale, or go out with someone. I think - we were rather a closely knit family and - er - not really a - we really didn't know many people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And your father's friends would he see them outside the house or would they come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
He'd mostly go - er - out with them - and - really secretly have a drink with them, you see, of course he had to keep that from mother, mother used to smell his breath when he came in. yes it was really dreadful. H
e was a very sociable man, father, he would have liked a much more sociable life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were the friends ever invited into the house into your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - we'd have people sometimes to tea on Sundays - that was the sort of - er - you know, special Sunday tea - never came to lunch or 
\'85\'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Would there be any particular days or occasions when they would come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - no. It was rather a set thing that it was a Sunday tea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did neighbours call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Occasionally - but not very often - usually if perhaps they wanted to borrow something or if they wanted to keep an eye on their dog while they went out, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 People often tell us in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours - not with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I t
hink they usually played at something - cards very often - cards were very popular - even telling fortunes by cards, that was a commonplace thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about music - would they make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. Yes. That was common too. Somebody would - er 
- play the piano or any instrument they happened to play - somebody would sing. I think all that was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh definitely, yes. We were brought up in that way - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Could you say what you think the differences were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, now, not quite working class - what they called the lower working class, the middle class people and the uppe
r class as they used to say. and then there were the aristocrats. At the top, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Which class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Just middle class I should think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What sort of people belonged to the same class group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Professional people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what sort of people would you say belonged to the other classes or groups that you've mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Trades. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And which class would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well - er - probably dress making tailoring - all those sort of th
ings - er - well or course engineering was rather a - course that's tremendously advanced now isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about working class occupations - what would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well they perhaps were very often servants, you see, 'cos that was a very common t
hing to be a servant or a launderer - going to go to the laundry and serve in shops - they were the usual kind of things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what about the upper classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - professions more you see - architects - er - mathematicians I suppose - teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
There was a sort of feeling, I suppose, of - of great respect for some people - perhaps professional people if they were - er - doing something more interesting or which required better brains - I think threw were quite distinctions in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 As a child were you ever told to behave in a particular way - to show respect in some way to - a - ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not so much told as it was --er- somehow implied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what would you do - what would you show as a sign of respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well, mother or father might say oh he's a very clever fellow or something like that - He's got a - er - several degrees and we'd feel a little bit awed - it was - er - there was a great respect for intellect I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was there anyone ever that you called Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these particular ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, because I think they mingled with similar pe
ople you see, similar type people, so that - it was more - the servants would say Sir or - or the char ladies - Madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 In this area where you lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Enfield{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, who were considered the most important people, do you remember, were there any people who were considered to be very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
No, I don't think so - I think they were mostly - er - similar types of people - as far as I can remember. No - not like Highgate because Highgate has had important people hasn't it. Lived here - but not {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Enfield{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Sort of mostly rather middle class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was there a chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I wouldn't know about the chapel because we were high church so you had a very mixed - in the high church - you 
had rather - on the whole - rather better off people - people who were earning more - rather more money I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And where you lived did all the people in the working or lower working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were 
different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I think there were groups rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956 ould you describe sort of rough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 ly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well there were certain people who would buy the fried fish and chips you know in paper and that sort of thing and then the grade above them would
 not do that. Er - there were differences in that way. And there were sort of eating houses for poorer people and restaurants for better - certainly more better class people - that has all rather died out hasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the next?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, definitely, I think so, I think superiority was something people seemed to value and - er - it was quite snobbish in a way.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Oh quite. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and Labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Craftsmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
 were respected though. Yes. I think craftsmen have always been respected. Yes, and still today, people who can really make things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I think they felt very much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, I think she would just consider herself middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you think it was because of her parentage or because of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh I think both. Yes. Yes. You see her father was a writer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think through marriage, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Can you think of anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I don't think I can actually, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you ever remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well because I think they had very nice manners and were - used to - er - authority - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well - we felt he was a great protector.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You looked on him as a protector?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes. Ever I - I think that children - some children were frightened with policeman because they were told the policeman would be after them but we were not told that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You looked on him as a \'85..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, as a benefactor - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
The policeman? Well I only know he was very kind to - er - children - the ones we knew - used to take me across the road - I was rather a dashing little thing and risked 
the traffic and there were one or two policeman who were very good to me and said they'd saved my life several times. But I know that mothers often did say that a policeman would be after you and I think perhaps they were rougher in those days. Well life 
was tougher in many ways - many people anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was the house you lived in rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, but then father bought it you see, he was offered to buy it, paying rent and paying so much off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So you don't remember the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
No, I don't - I - well - I don't know anything about that - I think - I don't know whether father paid it by cheque or what happened. All I knew was that father told us that he was buying the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember feeling ever that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well sometimes I think you see, when the rates came in that - er - there wasn't always quite enough money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did you think about it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I don't think it wor
ried us, somehow, we - it was one of those things that happened to grown ups - father never talked about these things much - he simply say oh be the rates soon and - er - it'll be a bit overdue or something like that but he didn't - he never grumbled abou
t it so that we didn't - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He sounds a lovely man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He was a very nice person yes. He was very philosophical. And kind - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What difference did it make to the family if your father was ever ill or out of work? Was he ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, 
he had bronchial asthma - oh it was very difficult because he didn't have any money - wasn't earning any money - that was - but of course mother used to belong to one of these - er - clubs that gave you money - that helped out but of course it was difficu
lt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was he ever out of work do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Er - no. But he was - he was - only with illness. He was very, very good at his job and liked you see and - but he did get very bad attacks of bronchial asthma - and was not able to go and of course there was no help in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You didn't get help from the Guardians of the Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, nothing like that, no - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, of course today it's much easier isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. People out of work often had to go to the work-house. When Kei
th complains about things today I say you read your history - I've seen people begging in the street - going round singing and playing an instrument and begging - or the monkey - that was another thing - they used to have these little monkeys, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And was it a frequent sight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes, quite common. I was always so sorry for the poor little monkeys. The people put money in because of the monkey - they liked to see the monkey perform, you see. Oh those music boxes, I remember those, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were you given lesson by one of your parents or a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, we went to school, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think I was about seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And when you first started what time in the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh it must have been about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Um - I think about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past four{\*\xmlclose} we left off, something like that. It was a long day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you come home for lunch in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And how long would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I can't remember - I think it was about an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 It was a kindergarten perhaps - yes - er - um - I don't know - a kindergarten school - a little private school I think it was actually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Walked. It wasn't very far - about a quarter or an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We went together you see. 'Cos there was only a little difference in our ages eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you had your mid-day meal at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Yes. They had no school meals, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did you have to eat at mid-day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Just the conventional diet, you know, we had meat and vegetables and suet puddings - hateful suet puddings - sometime
s milk puddings which I hated - Rice and all those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I liked school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Why? Do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well - I liked people and I liked to do things, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You were a very active child weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Y
es. But I loved reading and books - I liked some lessons better than others - I didn't like arithmetic very much but on the whole I liked school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did you think about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well some teachers of course I fairly loved and others I did
n't like. If they were kind and understanding I liked them - if they were very strict and sharp and - I didn't. I loved gymnastics - and that was when I was - early days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did the teachers emphasise anything as important in life - manners, tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh very much - yes - very much so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If you did something they disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well you were punished - either by being kept in or of course they would give you 
a - the ruler - slaps on your hand - that was horrid - or you'd be kept in or have to do extra homework or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was it the same for the boys as the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. I think they were a bit more severe with the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What sort of things would you have been punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well, if you were late or if you weren't paying attention or if you were talking. Or if you fidgeted too much or if you spilled the ink - all sorts of things that happen to children, you know, we were quite severely reprimanded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not very much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 They didn't ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - they didn't - father was interested in - in books and drawing and that sort of thing and used to ask me about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Or the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did the other children at the school come from similar sorts of homes as yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I think so, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes, yes, they did. Sometimes a - er - a teacher would take a dislike to a child and perhaps the child was very difficult and - there were certainly plenty of punishments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. Er - some of them used to gang up together, yes - a few of the wilder ones and torment the more timid ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think so sometimes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Er - that was much better. Happier all together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When was that - how old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think when I was about twelve I went to another school - a better school all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What sort of school was that - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I don't quite know what it was called - but we had to pay of course. It wasn't a free school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And how did you get to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh that - I had to take a bus - I forget where it was actually - I had to take a bus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how long it took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh not long on the bus, perhaps quarter of an hour. Can't remember where that school was, but we were happy there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you come home for your mid-day meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did you think of this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I liked the second school I went to - I was very happy there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And the teachers in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes they were much nicer than in the other school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did they emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Of c
ourse they were all very keen on manners, behaving properly and sitting up straight and all that sort of thing and not moving until you were told to. They were very strict about all those sort of things. It's entirely different at schools today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If you did something the teachers disapproved of in this school would they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh we were always punished - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 In the same sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, exactly the same - yes. I think they were all very similar you see, some - you had to pay 
more than others and they were a bit more exclusive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When you were at this school did your parents show any interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not very much - no - father was always interested in the drawing and - and writing and that sort of thing but not very much actually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did the other children at that school come from the same sort of homes as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think - pretty much the same - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And again in this school did the teachers single out some children for different treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes, I think it was a very - very usual thing in those days. You see it was before much knowledge of psychology, wasn't it. And the teachers were very human.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were there any gangs in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think there were in most of 
them really but - er - some were a bit rougher than others. There were always some children that wanted to torment others, you know. Of course our teachers shut their eyes to it where now of course it wouldn't be - it wouldn't happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was this the last school you went to? Or did you go on to another one after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, I only went to - the two - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Let's see - how old was I - I think I was about - seventeen - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I would have liked to have gone to college you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you attend any part time education afterwards? Evening classes or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I used to go to a lot of lectures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956 Where about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Um - I can't remember the names of the institutes you know, they were places where they used to have lectures like - um - I can't remember at all. Lectures on literature and talks on art - er - polytechnics - yes - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you just took yourself off and \'85..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh yes, I used to go for the sheer love of it and they were very inexpensive you had to pay something but not very much and - er - parents quite agreed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I just think
 it'd been better - if - it was a pity they were not more advanced because it was - er - now it's - er - delightful - it must be lovely to go to school now. I think the revolution in education has been simply tremendous. You see you had to learn so much b
y repetition - they didn't try to get your interest - it was just the set - the set rule - and that's pretty exhausting and it's not the best way to learn is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh I'm sure - yes, yes, I couldn't possibly have learnt so many things on my own. I've certainly -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956  would probably never have tack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 led arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You didn't h
ave a first full time job, am I correct or not, you lived at home until you were twenty-six but did you have a job after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You just lived at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. I - I - I helped in - at home. And I made all the family's clothes. 
And I did the cooking and helped mother run the house and so on. That was because I was the most domestic of the - the others had professions. One was the first woman - um - she did the books at the Old Vic - bookkeeper - the first woman they ever had at 
t
he Old Vic - so she got ever such a lot of tickets you see, lovely expensive tickets. She was rather masculine, rather square, not in the way we use it now - square in build. Rather masculine looking and she enjoyed her job very much. Er - she was very ha
ppy and the - another one became a teacher - she liked her job - she became very eccentric and - had to go further and further out - but she was a very good teacher up to - er - and you see I was at home and the boys died so \'85\'85\'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What jobs have you done since the first world war? Have you done any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Except you were telling me you wrote a lot of recipes - you've written a\'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, I did all that - I wrote recipes - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you had a book published?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - the Attractive Fo
od Reform and then the - er - little sixpenny book was - um - How to Live Economically on Good Food and that sold for sixpence I think then - I didn't get any royalties on that but it - er - yes there was a copy of that in my caravan somebody found - I su
ppose I've got a copy somewhere. I wrote recipes for Nursery World - yes - er - that was monthly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How long did you do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I did that for two or three years and then they changed the editor and so they thought they'd have somebody else to do
 recipes and they were conventional ones and several of the women wrote up to say that they were so sorry they still hadn't got Maud Baines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what time was that - when were you writing for the Nursery World?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Goodness, I can't remember. I'm sorry - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Would you have preferred to have had a job - would you have liked to have had a job as such?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I don't know - I would have liked to have been a painter, you see. I would have liked to have gone to an art school, very much I
 would have liked that, more than anything else. I didn't want to be a teacher - don't think I wanted to do anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You would have liked to have gone to an art school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If you didn't work you presumably didn't belong to any Trade Union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, no, no. I didn't belong to anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 After you left school - your home}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5182195\charrsid10370956  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 life - you did say you spent it slightly differently? That you still continued to do the same sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you went out in the evening and you sometimes went to concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Kings Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You didn't meet many new friends but you did have several friends who were quite a lot older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And special friends who were sometimes as much as twenty or thirty?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And your parents didn't really take much interest in your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But they did expect to know where you were and you had to be home by a certain time - right. So you married in 1913 when you 
were twenty-six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you said you had known your husband for two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 At a Literary Society - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And he came from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you save up money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - because I wasn't earning any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But your husband did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your parents help you in setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - but they - there was no need.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Not very long - I can't remember exactly - because Billy was anxious to get married - I should think it would be about a year, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Could you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - I can't remember quite where we were married - it was a dear little church, I do remember that - I think it was St Albans
 because - er - he was living there - er - and then we had a flat there you see, for the time being.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. We had - um - he had two nieces whom he'd fathered because they - their father had died you see, and - they were ver
y upset at the marriage because they thought he was a natural bachelor - everybody thought he was - and they were very upset and they've never - they never quite forgave me. They're still alive. Er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were your mother and father there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. And just a few people - it was quite a small quiet wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have presents and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. Yes, we went away - now where did we go to - um - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Seaford{\*\xmlclose} - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And where did you live after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, we lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}St Albans{\*\xmlclose} in a flat for a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And how many years did you \'85.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - we didn't live there very long - it was about - I think only about a year and then - er - we were - Billy was very keen on liv
ing in Highgate and we got a little flat up in Highgate Village overlooking Waterlow Park. And we lived there for several years until Billy could buy this house, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember how long - if you moved to Highgate in 1914 it would be wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How long did you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I think we were there - up in the village for about three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And then you came here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - yes. I - it wasn't - we hadn't got quite enough money to buy the house until then - and he had very m
uch foresight because he was fifteen years my senior and he know that he would die before me and I would have no professional training - he knew I liked people so he bought a house large enough for me to let. That's how I live because I'm not eligible for
 
any pensions or anything like that at all, you see, I depend entirely on the house - but because I like people and am pretty tolerant and all that - he thought I would make a living so it showed very great foresight - because I do live on the house, you s
ee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Your husband was fifteen years older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So he would have been forty-one when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, he was - it was either fifteen or fourteen, I can't quite remember, but it was quite a bit anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What was your husbands job when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
He was an architect. But of course he was working for somebody else - he was working - I forget the firm - and he was very versatile because they weren't so specialized in those days - he could do churches and houses a
nd all kinds of things - he was very badly paid but he loved his work and that was the important thing and he had got the - he had an opportunity of getting on to the council and he let me make the decision - he would have got regular money - good money a
nd a pension when he'd finished but he wouldn't have enjoyed the work - so I said well it's so important for you to enjoy your life and we can do with less money - and I \'85..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 This was - oh I can't remember. When we'd been married so
me few years - um - he had this chance and of course he would have had a good pension - but you see I think if a man's got to earn his living all his life and he - it's - he would have had just certain kinds of work where he did everything, you see - he w
ould have been just on houses or on churches or something like that and he was so grateful that I made the decision. Well, it's much better to have less money and be satisfied in your job - isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did he have any other jobs before or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No
, he'd kept this one all the way through - he was such a faithful and good worker and so versatile, you see, he was very clever. Was a very good man indeed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How do you think your husband felt about his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He enjoyed it - oh yes - he enjoyed his work very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 You had two children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Just the two - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Can you tell me when they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh dear -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 One born in about 1915?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And one about 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, yes. There were no more after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. I had a midwife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well not really, very much - I knew how it came of course - I didn't know it was going to be so painful - 'cos they never talked about that then you see. And of course they didn't - er - know so much about drugs to help you in those days either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But you had a midwife in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - midwife - she was very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your husband help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - he wasn't even allowed in the room. He wa
s in agony - walking up and down - course now the husbands sit with them - well they didn't just - or - it just wasn't the right thing at all - I think it's a great help to have your husband near you - because it was terrible for him - he was in a state o
f perspiration.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How soon were you out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I don't - does it matter much? I recovered very quickly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How did you manage while you were in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I had this - um - daily nurse who came in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did any of your relations or neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And a nurse came in every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh, every day - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 For how long - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well for some time - but I recovered very quickly and was still able - quite able to cope quite soon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did the nurse do for the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh bath it and so on, you see, I fed it of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you fed your first child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Breast fed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I fed them both for nine months. Mm. Breast fed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you enjoy feeding them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have any difficulties in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
No. None at all - I had plenty of milk - well there were no tensions you see - I believed in it and I had the milk and it was all perfectly all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If you needed any advice to do with the baby who would you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I suppose the doctor. But somehow I didn't seem to need it at all went quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If the baby was asleep would you wake it for a feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If it cried before the normal time would you feed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 If it cried in a certain way and I knew it was hungry - yes. Not otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What would you do if it didn't seem hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well - I used to - er - let it sleep but - at first - and then I found that, you see, perhaps you had to feed it in the middle of the night
 - so I tried to arrange it that it slept at a certain time - and - er - I don't know, it seemed to work out really quite well without any trouble, somehow, it seemed to wake naturally at the right time - I don't really remember experiencing much difficul
ty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How long would you let the baby feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well that I wouldn't remember - but just until they felt - felt sleepy. Mm. You see they're so different - Fiona was very vigourous - Keith was not nearly so strong and he was more feeble so he went on longer. I just let the baby decide.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 When did you first give the baby solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Goodness, I can't remember - but I think \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But it was fed after nine months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, I fed them for a long time because I so much believed in that. And very gradually introduced the other foods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So you weaned babies at nine months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was it sudden or was it gradual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, gradually - that's so much better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did the baby mind - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Preferred the natural feeding all the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you think at that time it did any harm to the baby to let it cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I didn't think it should cry too long, 'cos I think it's very exhausting to cry too long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you punish it if it was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How much did your husband have to do with your children? When they were babies under one year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well he didn't really have - except that he always spent a little time with them, and - er - liked to be there and so on. He was very, very fond 
of them and used to take them out - and he would take them in the pram out while I cooked the Sunday dinner and so on. Oh he was terribly fond of them, very proud of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But before they were a year old he didn't really - he didn't help you - I mean with particular things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, no he couldn't really. But he was very concerned and very - much there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 About your housekeeping before 1919. Did you know what your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I think I did - I can't remember what it was. I know tha
t I could always manage - he didn't earn very much, but I was - I was a very good manager you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you know how much of what he earned he would give to you? What proportion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well he would give me as much as he could, I know that - he was a ve
ry generous man. I think he worked out all the expenses and I just took what I could manage on, you see, because I always \'85\'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you discuss with him how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, in a most friendly way - we never had any troubles like
 that, we were both anxious to - he was a most generous man. And I was a very good manager. Well, I never had any difficulties of that kind. But the actual amount - I really couldn't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How many rooms are there in this house - this is the house you moved to in about 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Now how many rooms are there? There's the flat downstairs with - um - two rooms, kitchen - that's three - this has there - that's six - upstairs there's three - that's nine - um - perhaps you'll help me reckon it up. Shal
l we start at the top - there's an attic - lovely large attic you see which I have a - one lady in - we've made a little kitchenette at the end of it, you see, she had to share the bathroom. Below that there's a two roomed flat - it's two rooms kitchen an
d bathroom, you see, and there's two flats upstairs - there's this flat and one downstairs so that's four flats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 So there would be eight rooms and an attic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 In 1917 to 18 were there any relatives or lodgers living with you when you first moved to this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Oh we had to get people at once you see - we kept this flat and the downstair flat and let the two upstairs flats - we kept the attic. For visitors to stay you know, and that - all that sort of thing, and let the two flats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, I had - um - I had a woman - er - to help you see with the work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did she live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh no, she didn't live in. I didn't like living in people. No, she came in everyday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What were her duties generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Well - mostly to do the housework because I wouldn't let anybody do the cooking. Because I was very keen on doing the right sort of cooking you see and I did the lighter work and she just did the heavier work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what did you call each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 She used to call me Mrs Baines - not Madam - just Mrs Baines - and I called her by her name - Mrs - well whatever she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Some of it was done at home but some of it - er - was sent out to the laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 The bigger stuff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - the sheets and big things were sent out. Other was done - I did it or the woman did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you continue to make and mend clothes yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Make all my own clothes and the children\rquote 
s. Of course I couldn't make Keith's when he went into proper suits - they had to be bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you buy new ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh I was very good at going to the Caledonian Market and picking up remnants you see and at Liberty's sale where they sell t
hings very cheaply at the last two or three days and I had a machine and I I was very good at making - dress making - and all this - I didn't have any lessons but I just did it naturally. And I didn't follow conventions very much - I made all my own cloth
es and I wore cloaks when nobody else ever wore them and I wore my hair down my back when everybody else was wearing it up on top. I've never troubled about fashions very much. It's awfully difficult now because I can't see the colours you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you ever buy any clothes in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, a winter coat. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And where would you buy that - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well at the sales usually, perhaps {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Liberty{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}'s or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Marshall{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and Snelgrove - some - where like that - and wear it for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what about shoes do you remember where you bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
Yes, I'm very difficult with shoes - I've got a very small foot and I wore sandals for years you see, Clarke's sandals, but Clarke's sandals are very bad now, you know, I tried to get some l
ast year - somebody took me all the way - I walked - Oxford Street one side and all down the other and I couldn't get any sandals that were comfortable. They were too fashionable. I've got very small feet and very - yes they're quite small and quite undef
ormed because I wore sandals for years. And I made all my clothes and all Fiona's clothes. I never had any lessons it was just natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your husband help with jobs in house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh - I wouldn't let him because he worked so hard that I felt it was unfair to him - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 He didn't do things like the fires?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh he would do that yes, we had an anthracite stove and he would make that up and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Decorating did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, because he was delicate and he worked so ha
rd. I did decorating - in fact I did decorating right until I lost my sight - I decorated nearly everything in the house - I decorated this room - I couldn't do the ceiling - I had to have men in for that - but you see, now I have to pay for everything to
 be done - I loved it - this was the last job I did - this room. I expect it wants doing again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about repairs to the house? And improvements to this house when you first moved in? Would your husband do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - well - yes he could do some 
of it - well he'd design and - er - and - er - overhaul and get things done you see - he was quite good at woodwork - he loved woodwork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you ask the children to do anything, did they have any special tasks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, I taught them both to cook -
 I thought that was very useful - and I taught Fiona how to help to make her clothes. Not that she did because when she married - Michael - he wanted her to be - not wear the sort of clothes she was - but very fashionable things you see so they were bough
t
, but she could make her own clothes and she - they could both cook awfully well, I let them help me cook you see - I didn't say you've got to cook or anything like that but would you like to come and help me cook and they are both very good cooks. You se
e if they think they are doing it and they enjoy it and haven't got to do it I think that's the way to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember what time the children went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Er - they went to bed early - I believed in that - they had a bedtime story before going to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What time would be early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well - er - it depended upon their ages, of course, when they were \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Fiona, for instance, who was born in 1915 when - what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh about seven - something like that - yes. But then we'd have a story or something, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did your husband ever put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes - sometimes he did over the weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did they share a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No they had separate rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about sleeping arrangements for the whole family - they would have separate bedrooms and you and your husband had the same bedroom?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Our bedroom, yes, yes. Keith had the little room you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And was there a bathroom when you moved into this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes, there was only one bathroom - 'course we had to have more put in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 How often did the children have baths when they were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh most evenings I would bath them before going to bed. Well they enjoyed it the job was to get them out again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember when they had clean clothes - would you put clean clothes on regularly or just when they got dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, regularly in the winter but more often in the summer - because, you know, you got - thin things and you get hot and \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Do you remember where you ate meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We did have our meals at regular times - I rather believed in that. And not bits between meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have a dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Were there any occasions when they'd be eaten in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No, we kept to the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And you cooked in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have a range or gas there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh it was a big range but it was lovely and - er - you it was - downstairs was the big kitchen and then there was a scull
ery with an old - er - of course copper in it you see, it was old fashioned 7/8 and then there was the breakfast room so you see we used to have the breakfast room - we used to have the meals in there and then Billy and I on the evening meal would have it
 upstairs. Of course that was - we had the meals in the breakfast room usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh I think it was about seven or something or about half past, I can't quite remember. The children - plenty of time for the childre
n - I didn't believe in rushing meals and - er - they got to school at nine you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What did you give your family for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well they had - um - brown - always wholemeal bread - I made most of my own wholemeal bread - if I - or I got Allis
ons, you see, which was a very good bread - I didn't believe in porridge 'cos its' too soft and they had - er - some fruit - er - prunes or dates or things like that and apples perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And did you and your husband have the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. We all 
had the same kind of thing. Er - Billy and I - I had china tea - Billy liked coffee - the children had milk - they didn't have tea or coffee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you have anything different on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 We used to have a more leisurely breakfast on Sunday. 
Yes, well it was a sort of - there was more time, you see, and the children had a salad every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Would that be at mid-day or in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well, it depends where they were you see. When they went to the King Alfred they had very good food th
ere, they had lots of salads and so on and I arranged what they would have there - if they had a salad there they had a cooked meal in the evening, you see, if they had a cooked meal there they had a salad in the evening. Every day they had a salad - ever
yday they had fresh fruit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What would you and your husband eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh the same things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What would you have mid-day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well he, of course had to have his meal out as he was working - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well I would have either a fruit meal or a salad meal or just a stew - a conservatively cooked stew, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 What about in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Well we had our best meal in the evening when the children were older, but we had, when the children - of course when they went 
to the King Alfred they had very good food there you see, so they had their meal there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But when you were first married - you and your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh I was full ready for the reform before I was married you see, oh yes. I got - well I was so delica
te and always - being so ill and I studied food reform and got very much better, you see, I felt that\'85\'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 It's incredible to think that you were ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh, I was always being ill - I had lung trouble and all sorts of things. I was ill more than any
 of the rest of the family, but of course I've out lived them all. But then I was aware of it you see and just changed things. Yes, yes. Of course it's terribly sad when your children marry and then go and live conventionally - 'cos then you see them losi
n
g their health - it's a natural reaction I suppose, but it's a pity. Unless of course, you see, my trouble was that I didn't like the ordinary vegetarians because they talked about nothing but food and you see I was interested in other things and if I'd b
e
come like a lot of them did, a regular vegetarian, they'd have probably married vegetarians but you see the ordinary early vegetarians didn't live very healthily - they just left out meat - they boiled their vegetables and lost most of the minerals, just 
like ordinary people do and they just had cheese and eggs instead of meat, you see, and the weren't awfully healthy, so I didn't really belong to any of them and that was so difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 But you did make your own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Did you make your own jam and pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I didn't have jam - I didn't believe in jam - I didn't believe in white sugar, you see, it's deprived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Oh not pickles - no - nothing with vinegar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Home made wines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 I didn't make wine - no - but - we were teetotallers then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 Medicines - did you make your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 
I didn't make medicines - I didn't believe in them. I - er - now what did I give the children. They very rarely had colds - I think I gave them peppermint I gave - er - herbs - I believe in herbs - some herbal concoction - but they very rarely had a cold.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16742072 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 And what about bottled fruit and vegetables - did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211231 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5198017\charrsid10370956 No - no, I believed in everything fresh. No.
